2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper discusses the challenges faced by visual SLAM algorithms and proposes a way to integrate Wi-Fi sensing into such algorithms. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper utilizes Wi-Fi received signal strength to improve the accuracy and efficiency of visual SLAM algorithms, which is relevant to the field of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a generic way to integrate Wi-Fi sensing into visual SLAM algorithms, which may involve machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the development of spatial applications on mobile devices and robots, which may involve systems and control techniques.
